[signal arg="show_title_card 4"]
# Initialize variable (will be overwritten by init_character_var signal)
set {selected_character} = ""
[signal arg="init_character_var"]
[background arg="res://Bg/library_archive.png" fade="2.0"]
set {chapter4_score} = 0
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 a week after.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
A week after the broken sculpture case...
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4SO THE LIBRARY ARCHIVE.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
The library archive is quiet, dusty, and forgotten. Shelves tower in the dim light, packed with decades of records.
join Mystery (sillhouette) center [animation="Fade In" length="1.0" wait="true"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 ALEX SEARCHES THROUGH.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
A mysterious person searches through old filing cabinets, looking for reference materials for a history project.
Mystery (sillhouette): Let's see... 1995, 1996... no, too recent. I need something from the early 90s.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 SHE PULLS OPEN.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
She pulls open a drawer that resists at first, then jerks open with a groan.
Mystery (sillhouette): What's this?
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 A LEATHER BOUND JOURNAL.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
A leather-bound journal sits wedged behind the files, hidden deliberately.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 ALEX CAREFULLY LIFTS.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Mysterious person carefully lifts it out, brushing off dust.
Mystery (sillhouette): "Educational Philosophy and Moral Development." No author listed.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 SHE OPENS THE JOURNAL.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
She opens to the first page and begins reading.
Mystery (sillhouette): "Observation teaches lessons that lectures cannot. Students learn best when challenged to think, not told what to think."
Mystery (sillhouette): This is... interesting.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 SHE FLIPS THROUGH.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
She flips through pages filled with psychological puzzles, moral dilemmas, and notes about student behavior.
Mystery (sillhouette): "Case Study 3\: Student A cheated because they feared disappointing their parents. Rather than punish, I created a scenario where honesty was rewarded."
Mystery (sillhouette): Whoever wrote this was trying to teach through experience, not authority.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 SHE CONTINUES READING.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
She continues reading, fascinated.
Mystery (sillhouette): "The best lessons come from discovery. When students solve problems themselves, they internalize the moral far deeper than any lecture could achieve."
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 HER GRIP TIGHTENS.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 OBSERVING THEIR REACTIONS.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 ALEX PAUSES.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Mysterious person thinks of Conrad and his detective work - solving cases that taught real lessons.
Mystery (sillhouette): Conrad does this. He helps people learn by uncovering truth.
Mystery (sillhouette): What if... what if I could do something similar?
Mystery (sillhouette): These puzzles, these challenges... I could use them to help other students grow.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4SO SHE CLOSES THE JOURNAL.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
She closes the journal, decision made.
Mystery (sillhouette): The person who wrote this understood something important. Knowledge isn't just about facts.
Mystery (sillhouette): It's about becoming better people through experience.
Mystery (sillhouette): I'm going to continue what they started.
leave Mystery [animation="Fade Out" length="0.8"]
[background arg="res://Bg/hallway.png" fade="2.0"]
[wait time="1.0"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 the next day.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
The next day...
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 anonymous notes begin.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Anonymous notes begin appearing in student lockers.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 each one contains.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Each one contains a puzzle, a challenge, a moral question.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 the students who receive.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
The students who receive them are confused, curious, and some are frightened.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/c4s0 they dont understand.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
They don't understand who is testing them, or why.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4s0 BUT SOMEONE IS WATCHING.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
But someone is watching. Observing their reactions.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 4/C4S0/C4S0 TAKING NOTES.mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Taking notes, just like the journal taught.
[wait time="1.5"]
jump c4s1/